      "description": "Learn how closures work in JavaScript with practical examples",
      "content": "Understanding Closures in JavaScript Closures are one of the most powerful concepts in JavaScript. A closure is a function that has access to variables in its outer scope, even after the outer function has returned. Basic Example Key Concepts - Lexical scope - Function scope - Memory management - Practical applications Closures enable data privacy and are commonly tested in technical interviews.",
